interaction_id: Unique identifier for each conversation in the CANDOR corpus ; all sequences from the same interaction share this ID
initiating_speaker: Which participant initiated the sequence (coded as left/right based on video orientation).
sequence_type: The type of conversational sequence identified by RAs (e.g., question sequence, disclosure–uptake sequence).
sequence_start: Timestamp (in seconds from conversation start) marking when the initiating turn of the sequence begins.
sequence_end: Timestamp (in seconds) marking when the sequence ends (after the relevant response/uptake occurs).
sequence_duration: Length of the sequence in seconds (sequence_end – sequence_start).
speaker_said: Short excerpt from the initiating speaker’s turn, provided only as context to help you understand the sequence. (Do not analyze this text in Q3; analyze the sequence structure and patterns instead.)
